The restless Gebreselassie has improved his world record
Haile Gebreselassie of Ethiopia once again showed why many consider him the best distance runner ever when he broke his own world record at the Berlin Marathon on Sunday, becoming the first man to run a 26.2-mile race in under two hours and four minutes.
