He was also criticized - particularly in Kenya, the East African rival of Ethiopia - for allegedly over-planning his races, generally avoiding the world marathon peaks, relying on drivers as if it were a track race, and setting world records above the point of competition.
But this criticism can hardly diminish Gebreselassie's enormous running quality.
Maintained at the pace of four Kenyan, Gebreselassie reached halfway through the race in 1:02:04.
After the drivers failed, Gebreselassie was constantly pursued by two elite Kenyan runners James Kwambai and Charles Kamathi.
