Domestic sales prices in the industry increased by only a minimum of 0.1% compared to the previous month.
The domestic sales prices in the manufacturing sectors also increased slightly, by 0,1%, compared to July.
The largest price increase was in August 2008 in the leather and footwear industry (2,8%) mainly due to monthly price increases in the silk and cotton and footwear industries of 4,6% and 2,5% respectively.
The higher price levels of plastics and chemicals have caused a significant monthly increase in prices in the chemical materials and products sector (1.6%).
Prices fell in the oil processing sector (1.4%), electrical machinery and appliances (0.9%) and, to a lesser extent, in the woodworking sector (0.1%).
