In the consumer goods sectors, we saw a price increase of 6.8%, while in the physical assets, we saw a price decline of 1.4%.
The export sales prices of industrial products measured in forints increased by 1,1% in August compared to the previous month and decreased by 3,9% in the 12-month period.
